text: We were using Firebase for a few features: student presence, snapshots, and polygraph updates. Those features were broken for an additional couple of hours. We just finished migrating our heaviest usage features away from Firebase, so tomorrow should hopefully be smooth sailing.

text: The cause: we overwhelmed the Firebase service on which we rely for a handful of features, which caused an increased load on our servers, temporarily overwhelming our autoscaling systems. By bypassing Firebase, we were able to get most of our sites back up.
